article_title: Making Financial Advisers and Investment Bankers Better Teammates
article_text:
“I-bankers look at us as second-class citizens,” a financial adviser from one of the big brokerages recently said to me, referring to his colleagues in investment banking.

If you are a wealth manager at a major financial institution who has phoned an I-banker without going through proper channels or listened to your boss rant after he or she was excoriated by a liaison from those hallowed halls, then you know exactly what the adviser...
